# WPShadow Commit Message Template

# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <philosophy>
# <footer>

# TYPES (use lowercase):
#   feat:     A new feature (new diagnostic, treatment, system)
#   fix:      A bug fix (correctness, security, performance)
#   refactor: Code restructuring (no feature change, better DRY)
#   docs:     Documentation changes (README, guides, KB links)
#   style:    Code style changes (spacing, formatting, linting)
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   test:     Test additions or fixes
#   chore:    Build, dependencies, or tooling changes

# SCOPE (examples):
#   (diagnostic)    - Add/fix a diagnostic check
#   (treatment)     - Add/fix a treatment/auto-fix
#   (workflow)      - Workflow automation system
#   (kanban)        - Kanban board UI/logic
#   (kpi)           - KPI tracking system
#   (ajax)          - AJAX handler
#   (ui)            - User interface improvements
#   (security)      - Security improvements
#   (architecture)  - Architecture changes
#   (docs)          - Documentation

# SUBJECT LINE RULES:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add feature" not "added feature")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter after type
#   - No period (.) at the end
#   - Limit to 50 characters

# BODY (wrap at 72 chars):
#   - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   - Reference related issues: "Fixes #123"
#   - Separate from subject with blank line

# PHILOSOPHY CHECK:
#   Add one line indicating which commandment(s) this serves:
#
#   Philosophy: Helpful Neighbor (#1) - links to KB
#   Philosophy: Free as Possible (#2) - no paywalls
#   Philosophy: Show Value (#9) - tracks time saved
#   etc.
#
#   Or if refactoring/chore, explain code health:
#
#   Philosophy: Code Quality - 15% DRY improvement

# FOOTER (optional):
#   Closes #123
#   Related-To: #456
#   Breaking-Change: describe any breaking changes

# EXAMPLES:

# Example 1: New diagnostic
# feat(diagnostic): add ssl certificate expiration check
#
# Checks if site's SSL certificate expires within 30 days and
# recommends renewal. Helps prevent unexpected downtime.
#
# Includes automatic renewal link and KB article reference.
#
# Philosophy: Helpful Neighbor (#1) - educates on SSL importance
#             Show Value (#9) - prevents outages
#
# Closes #123

# Example 2: New treatment
# feat(treatment): auto-increase php memory limit to 256mb
#
# Safe treatment that increases PHP memory limit if currently below
# 256MB. Prevents common "allowed memory exhausted" errors.
#
# Includes full backup and undo capability. Tracks 10 minutes saved.
#
# Philosophy: Ridiculously Good (#7) - safe auto-fix with undo
#             Show Value (#9) - tracks time saved
#
# Closes #456

# Example 3: Code quality improvement
# refactor(core): consolidate duplicate nonce verification patterns
#
# Extract 8 instances of duplicate nonce checking into AJAX_Handler_Base.
# Reduces code by 45 lines, improves security consistency.
#
# All AJAX handlers now extend base class with centralized verification.
#
# Philosophy: Code Quality - eliminated DRY violation across 8 files
#
# Related-To: #789

# Example 4: Security fix
# fix(security): add sanitization to widget output
#
# Widget title and description weren't being escaped before output.
# Potential XSS vulnerability.
#
# Now uses esc_attr() for all user-facing output.
#
# Philosophy: Beyond Pure (#10) - security comes first
#
# Closes #321
